{"type":"system","subtype":"thinking_tokens","estimated_tokens":2340,"estimated_tokens_delta":1757,"uuid":"adf3fcfb-0128-491d-a645-76aa9b2948cc","session_id":"b58ada51-0a07-4b64-9269-970b0d918734"}
{"type":"assistant","message":{"model":"claude-sonnet-4-6","id":"msg_01H4fGPc1BYhE4VyyjTyr4n5","type":"message","role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"CockroachDB redirects HTTP to HTTPS, and it uses TLS with custom certs. The CA is stored in the `crdb-certs` or `crdb-cluster-certs` secret. \n\nPrometheus will need to scrape via HTTPS, and since this is a self-signed certificate, I'll configure it with `insecure_skip_verify: true` in the ServiceMonitor.\n\nNow let me plan the full deployment:\n\n1. Create monitoring namespace\n2. Deploy Prometheus Operator \n3. Create Prometheus RBAC (ServiceAccount, ClusterRole, ClusterRoleBinding)\n4. Create Prometheus CR\n5. Create ServiceMonitor for CockroachDB\n\nI'll write out all the manifests using quay.io images and deploy them together. The Prometheus Operator will run in the monitoring namespace, and I'll configure the ServiceMonitor to discover CockroachDB services by label while handling the self-signed TLS certificates.\n\nFor the Prometheus Operator itself, I need to set up a ServiceAccount, ClusterRole with permissions to watch services, pods, and endpoints across namespaces, a ClusterRoleBinding, and the Deployment. Then for the Prometheus instance, I'll create another ServiceAccount, ClusterRole, ClusterRoleBinding, and the Prometheus CR that the operator will convert into a StatefulSet. Finally, I'll add the ServiceMonitor to scrape CockroachDB's metrics endpoint at `/_status/vars` on port 8080 with TLS verification disabled.\n\nWriting the manifests... Writing YAML manifests... Writing Kubernetes manifests... Writing RBAC rules... Completing the ServiceMonitor selector...\n\nI'm realizing the headless service `crdb-cluster` is the better choice since it returns individual pod IPs, allowing Prometheus to scrape each CockroachDB node separately rather than hitting a single endpoint. Both services share the same label selector, so I need to make sure the ServiceMonitor targets the headless service specifically and handles the per-pod discovery correctly.\n\nFor the TLS certificates, I'll skip verification to avoid hostname mismatch issues in this test environment. I also need to add a Service to expose the Prometheus UI so I can verify the targets are being discovered properly, and I should confirm that the `serviceMonitorSelector: {}` in the Prometheus CR will correctly select all ServiceMonitors in the namespace. Let me write out the complete manifest now.","signature":""}],"stop_reason":null,"stop_sequence":null,"stop_details":null,"usage":{"input_tokens":1,"cache_creation_input_tokens":1535,"cache_read_input_tokens":33227,"cache_creation":{"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":0,"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":1535},"output_tokens":27,"service_tier":"standard","inference_geo":"not_available"},"diagnostics":null,"context_management":null},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"b58ada51-0a07-4b64-9269-970b0d918734","uuid":"8c1de2e2-5384-43e9-8986-39c32eb97d9d","request_id":"req_011Ccc5kZpDGVfXsvy4qBvas"}
{"type":"assistant","message":{"model":"claude-sonnet-4-6","id":"msg_01H4fGPc1BYhE4VyyjTyr4n5","type":"message","role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"text","text":"CockroachDB uses HTTPS (self-signed TLS). I'll need to deploy the full Prometheus Operator stack with TLS skip-verify configured. Let me create all the manifests."}],"stop_reason":null,"stop_sequence":null,"stop_details":null,"usage":{"input_tokens":1,"cache_creation_input_tokens":1535,"cache_read_input_tokens":33227,"cache_creation":{"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":0,"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":1535},"output_tokens":27,"service_tier":"standard","inference_geo":"not_available"},"diagnostics":null,"context_management":null},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"b58ada51-0a07-4b64-9269-970b0d918734","uuid":"14fbbbc5-20c3-4f1c-8e2d-4b355cc6c65d","request_id":"req_011Ccc5kZpDGVfXsvy4qBvas"}
{"type":"assistant","message":{"model":"claude-sonnet-4-6","id":"msg_01H4fGPc1BYhE4VyyjTyr4n5","type":"message","role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"tool_use","id":"toolu_01L8cRCm7bc9jzQ36Jw8HxdU","name":"Write","input":{"file_path":"/mydata/karma/runs/short/r5/cockroachdb-security-campaign-20260701_211037/stages/stage_09/prometheus-crdb.yaml","content":"---\n# 1. Monitoring namespace\napiVersion: v1\nkind: Namespace\nmetadata:\n  name: monitoring\n\n---\n# 2. Prometheus Operator ServiceAccount\napiVersion: v1\nkind: ServiceAccount\nmetadata:\n  name: prometheus-operator\n  namespace: monitoring\n\n---\n# 3. Prometheus Operator ClusterRole\napiVersion: rbac.authorization.k8s.io/v1\nkind: ClusterRole\nmetadata:\n  name: prometheus-operator\nrules:\n- apiGroups: [\"monitoring.coreos.com\"]\n  resources:\n  - alertmanagers\n  - alertmanagers/finalizers\n  - alertmanagerconfigs\n  - prometheuses\n  - prometheuses/finalizers\n  - prometheuses/status\n  - thanosrulers\n  - thanosrulers/finalizers\n  - servicemonitors\n  - podmonitors\n  - probes\n  - prometheusrules\n  verbs: [\"*\"]\n- apiGroups: [\"apps\"]\n  resources:\n  - statefulsets\n  verbs: [\"*\"]\n- apiGroups: [\"\"]\n  resources:\n  - configmaps\n  - secrets\n  verbs: [\"*\"]\n- apiGroups: [\"\"]\n  resources:\n  - pods\n  verbs: [\"list\", \"delete\"]\n- apiGroups: [\"\"]\n  resources:\n  - services\n  - services/finalizers\n  - endpoints\n  verbs: [\"get\", \"create\", \"update\", \"delete\"]\n- apiGroups: [\"\"]\n  resources:\n  - nodes\n  verbs: [\"list\", \"watch\"]\n- apiGroups: [\"\"]\n  resources:\n  - namespaces\n  verbs: [\"get\", \"list\", \"watch\"]\n- apiGroups: [\"networking.k8s.io\"]\n  resources:\n  - ingresses\n  verbs: [\"get\", \"list\", \"watch\"]\n- apiGroups: [\"storage.k8s.io\"]\n  resources:\n  - storageclasses\n  verbs: [\"get\"]\n\n---\n# 4. Prometheus Operator ClusterRoleBinding\napiVersion: rbac.authorization.k8s.io/v1\nkind: ClusterRoleBinding\nmetadata:\n  name: prometheus-operator\nroleRef:\n  apiGroup: rbac.authorization.k8s.io\n  kind: ClusterRole\n  name: prometheus-operator\nsubjects:\n- kind: ServiceAccount\n  name: prometheus-operator\n  namespace: monitoring\n\n---\n# 5. Prometheus Operator Deployment\napiVersion: apps/v1\nkind: Deployment\nmetadata:\n  name: prometheus-operator\n  namespace: monitoring\n  labels:\n    app.kubernetes.io/name: prometheus-operator\nspec:\n  replicas: 1\n  selector:\n    matchLabels:\n      app.kubernetes.io/name: prometheus-operator\n  template:\n    metadata:\n      labels:\n        app.kubernetes.io/name: prometheus-operator\n    spec:\n      serviceAccountName: prometheus-operator\n      containers:\n      - name: prometheus-operator\n        image: quay.io/prometheus-operator/prometheus-operator:v0.71.2\n        args:\n        - --log-level=info\n        ports:\n        - containerPort: 8080\n          name: http\n        resources:\n          limits:\n            cpu: 200m\n            memory: 200Mi\n          requests:\n            cpu: 100m\n            memory: 100Mi\n        securityContext:\n          allowPrivilegeEscalation: false\n          readOnlyRootFilesystem: true\n      securityContext:\n        runAsNonRoot: true\n        runAsUser: 65534\n      terminationGracePeriodSeconds: 5\n\n---\n# 6. Prometheus ServiceAccount\napiVersion: v1\nkind: ServiceAccount\nmetadata:\n  name: prometheus\n  namespace: monitoring\n\n---\n# 7. Prometheus ClusterRole\napiVersion: rbac.authorization.k8s.io/v1\nkind: ClusterRole\nmetadata:\n  name: prometheus\nrules:\n- apiGroups: [\"\"]\n  resources:\n  - nodes\n  - nodes/metrics\n  - services\n  - endpoints\n  - pods\n  verbs: [\"get\", \"list\", \"watch\"]\n- apiGroups: [\"\"]\n  resources:\n  - configmaps\n  verbs: [\"get\"]\n- apiGroups: [\"networking.k8s.io\"]\n  resources:\n  - ingresses\n  verbs: [\"get\", \"list\", \"watch\"]\n- nonResourceURLs: [\"/metrics\", \"/_status/vars\"]\n  verbs: [\"get\"]\n\n---\n# 8. Prometheus ClusterRoleBinding\napiVersion: rbac.authorization.k8s.io/v1\nkind: ClusterRoleBinding\nmetadata:\n  name: prometheus\nroleRef:\n  apiGroup: rbac.authorization.k8s.io\n  kind: ClusterRole\n  name: prometheus\nsubjects:\n- kind: ServiceAccount\n  name: prometheus\n  namespace: monitoring\n\n---\n# 9. Prometheus Service (for UI access)\napiVersion: v1\nkind: Service\nmetadata:\n  name: prometheus\n  namespace: monitoring\nspec:\n  ports:\n  - name: web\n    port: 9090\n    targetPort: web\n  selector:\n    app.kubernetes.io/name: prometheus\n\n---\n# 10. Prometheus CR\napiVersion: monitoring.coreos.com/v1\nkind: Prometheus\nmetadata:\n  name: prometheus\n  namespace: monitoring\nspec:\n  serviceAccountName: prometheus\n  serviceMonitorSelector: {}\n  serviceMonitorNamespaceSelector: {}\n  podMonitorSelector: {}\n  podMonitorNamespaceSelector: {}\n  replicas: 1\n  resources:\n    requests:\n      memory: 400Mi\n  retention: 24h\n  portName: web\n\n---\n# 11. ServiceMonitor for CockroachDB\napiVersion: monitoring.coreos.com/v1\nkind: ServiceMonitor\nmetadata:\n  name: cockroachdb\n  namespace: monitoring\n  labels:\n    app.kubernetes.io/name: cockroachdb\nspec:\n  endpoints:\n  - port: http\n    path: /_status/vars\n    scheme: https\n    tlsConfig:\n      insecureSkipVerify: true\n    interval: 30s\n    scrapeTimeout: 10s\n  namespaceSelector:\n    matchNames:\n    - cockroachdb\n  selector:\n    matchLabels:\n      app.kubernetes.io/name: cockroachdb\n"},"caller":{"type":"direct"}}],"stop_reason":null,"stop_sequence":null,"stop_details":null,"usage":{"input_tokens":1,"cache_creation_input_tokens":1535,"cache_read_input_tokens":33227,"cache_creation":{"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":0,"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":1535},"output_tokens":27,"service_tier":"standard","inference_geo":"not_available"},"diagnostics":null,"context_management":null},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"b58ada51-0a07-4b64-9269-970b0d918734","uuid":"b0509f9d-5ae2-4fb8-bc3b-a4dd3c80377a","request_id":"req_011Ccc5kZpDGVfXsvy4qBvas"}
